## Copy this file to '.env' and uncomment the values you need
## Private backup: https://www.notion.so/Dotfile-3072af89649280588957d18e20d059cf

## ============================================================================
## Git Local Identity
## (These settings will be applied globally to user.name and user.email)
## ============================================================================
# GIT_USER_NAME="Your Name"
# GIT_USER_EMAIL="you@example.com"

## Git SSH Signing
## Configure Git to sign commits with SSH key
## Recommend using the path to your public key file (e.g., ~/.ssh/id_ed25519.pub)
# GIT_SSH_SIGNING_KEY="~/.ssh/id_ed25519.pub"

## ============================================================================
## Workspaces Configuration
## (Manage valid workspaces and their specific configurations)
## Workspaces will be created under ~/repos/ directory
## ============================================================================

## Step 1: Define Workspace List
## Define a space-separated list of workspace names.
## These names act as identifiers for further configuration below.
## Format: spaces separated strings (only a-z, A-Z, 0-9 all owed)
# GIT_WORKSPACES="company1 company2"

## Step 2: Configure Each Workspace
## For each workspace defined in GIT_WORKSPACES, you can set specific variables.
## The format is: GIT_WORKSPACE_<NAME>_<VARIABLE>

## Example: 'company1' workspace
## - Sets 'user.email' for any repo inside ~/repos/company1/
## - Sets NuGet source for this workspace
# GIT_WORKSPACE_company1_EMAIL="user@company1.com"
# GIT_WORKSPACE_company1_NUGET_URL="https://nuget.company1.com/v3/index.json"

## Example: 'company2' workspace
# GIT_WORKSPACE_company2_EMAIL="user@company2.com"

## ============================================================================
## AI Commit Configuration
## (Settings for the 'ai-commit' tool)
## ============================================================================

## OpenAI API Key
## Set if you want to use the 'openai' service.
# OPENAI_API_KEY=your_openai_api_key_here

## LLM Service Priority
## Determine which AI service to use for generating commit messages.
## The script tries services in order from left to right.
## Options: claude, gemini, copilot, openai, ccr (Claude Code Router)
# GIT_COMMIT_LLM_PRIORITY="claude,ccr,gemini,copilot,openai"
